  jQuery Cheat Sheet ------- https://oscarotero.com/jquery/
  jQuery CDN links --------- http://code.jquery.com/

-- jQuery Defined --

  jQuery - one of the most widely used JS libraries

  Offers simpler syntax to...
    1) navigate a document
    2) select DOM elements
    3) handle events
    4) create animations
    5) make AJAX requests
    6) add and create plugins
    7) create cross-browser-supported functionality

  Library vs. Framework
    Library = a bag of tools you can use in your application 
    Framework = a suite of tools to build the entire application (like a workshop)



-- Waning Popularity --

  jQuery is not the cool kid on the block anymore
  Still used widely in web development



-- Getting jQuery --

    Download: https://code.jquery.com/
    Use: Version 2.2.4. uncompressed (use minified for production)

    CDN: link in curriculum



-- jQuery Object --

    "$" = alias for "jQuery"

    $() function



-- $(document).ready() --

    - keeps code from being executed until the DOM is loaded but before images are finished downloading
    - protects our code in place of an IIFE



-- Curriculum Code Examples (assume the inclusion of jQuery) --

  // Changing text/html

  document.getElementByTagName("element")[0].innerHTML = "Hello World";
    vs. 
  $("element").html("Hello World"); 

  // Changing CSS styling

  document.getElementByTagName("element")[0].style.color = "blue";
    vs. 
  $("element").css("color", "blue"); 